sql:
SELECT stock_symbol, company_name
FROM stocks
WHERE stock_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Star navigator" is a metaphorical reference to portfolio managers;
- "Constellation of stocks" represents the set of stocks managed by each portfolio manager;
- "Shimmering threads" symbolizes the day-to-day pricing information of stocks;
- "Evening glow" is a metaphor for the closing price of stocks;
- "Brightest peak" refers to the highest price a stock reached during the day;
- "Dimmest ebb" is an expressive term for the lowest price a stock reached during the day.
